snippet: Ending a bitterly fought, unconventional race, Kenneth P. Thompson, the Democratic nominee, claimed victory on Tuesday night in the race for Brooklyn district attorney – for the second time — over the longtime incumbent, Charles J. Hynes.
abstract: Ending a bitterly fought, unconventional race, Kenneth P. Thompson, the Democratic nominee, claimed victory on Tuesday night in the race for Brooklyn district attorney – for the second time — over the longtime incumbent, Charles J. Hynes.

headline.main: New York: Thompson Claims Victory Over Hynes, Again, for Brooklyn District Attorney
